The paper proposes a new algorithm for solving the weighted $\ell_1$ minimization problem, which is a common problem in signal processing and machine learning. The paper also discusses the accuracy of support estimates and their impact on the algorithm's performance. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with signal processing and communication. The paper also involves optimization and machine learning, which are covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SP (Signal Processing). The numerical simulations and comparisons with other algorithms suggest that the paper may also belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper discusses the theoretical properties of the algorithm, which may fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
